FBIS3-666 "drafr048_c_94029" FBIS-AFR-94-048 Document Type:Daily Report 11 Mar 1994 REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA De Klerk Welcomes Mangope Decision on Election MB1103142594 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in English 1400 GMT 11 Mar 94 MB1103142594 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network Language: English Article Type:BFN [Excerpts] President Lucas Mangope of Bophuthatswana is to recommend at an extraordinary meeting of Parliament in Mmabatho that the homeland participates in the election. [passage omitted] State President F. W. de Klerk has welcomed the decision by President Mangope, saying this meant that Bophuthatswana could now give its full support to the electoral process. Addressing a news conference in Pretoria, President de Klerk said that the decision removed the main reason for the current unrest in Bophuthatswana.
